<question>Thank you for the explanation. I understand the basic steps involved in writing a Tic Tac Toe game in C. Can you give me some more specific tips on how to write the functions to initialize the game board, draw the game board, get the player's move, make a move, and check for a winner?</question>
<respone>Sure, here are some more specific tips on how to write the functions to initialize the game board, draw the game board, get the player's move, make a move, and check for a winner in a Tic Tac Toe game in C:

**Initialize the game board:**

The `initialize_game_board()` function should simply fill the game board with dashes ('-'). You can do this with a nested for loop:

```c
void initialize_game_board(char board[BOARD_SIZE][BOARD_SIZE]) {
  for (int i = 0; i < BOARD_SIZE; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < BOARD_SIZE; j++) {
      board[i][j] = '-';
    }
  }
}
```

**Draw the game board:**

The `draw_game_board()` function should print the game board to the console. You can do this with another nested for loop:

```c
void draw_game_board(char board[BOARD_SIZE][BOARD_SIZE]) {
  printf("\n");
  for (int i = 0; i < BOARD_SIZE; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < BOARD_SIZE; j++) {
      printf("| %c ", board[i][j]);
    }
    printf("|\n");
  }
  printf("\n");
}
```

**Get the player's move:**

The `get_player_move()` function should prompt the player for their move and return the row and column of their choice. You can do this with the `scanf()` function:

```c
int get_player_move(char board[BOARD_SIZE][BOARD_SIZE], int player) {
  int row, column;
  printf("Player %c, enter your move: ", player);
  scanf("%d %d", &row, &column);

  // Validate the move.
  if (row < 0 || row >= BOARD_SIZE || column < 0 || column >= BOARD_SIZE || board[row][column] != '-') {
    printf("Invalid move. Please try again.\n");
    return get_player_move(board, player);
  }

  return row * BOARD_SIZE + column;
}
```

**Make a move:**

The `make_move()` function should update the game board with the player's move. You can do this by simply setting the corresponding element of the game board array to the player's symbol:

```c
void make_move(char board[BOARD_SIZE][BOARD_SIZE], int row, int column, int player) {
  board[row][column] = player;
}
```

**Check for a winner:**

The `check_winner()` function should check if the current player has won the game by having three of their symbols in a row, column, or diagonal. You can do this by checking all possible winning combinations:

```c
int check_winner(char board[BOARD_SIZE][BOARD_SIZE]) {
  // Check the rows.
  for (int i = 0; i < BOARD_SIZE; i++) {
    if (board[i][0] == board[i][1] && board[i][1] == board[i][2] && board[i][0] != '-') {
      return board[i][0];
    }
  }

  // Check the columns.
  for (int i = 0; i < BOARD_SIZE; i++) {
    if (board[0][i] == board[1][i] && board[1][i] == board[2][i] && board[0][i] != '-') {
      return board[0][i];
    }
  }

  // Check the diagonals.
  if (board[0][0] == board[1][1] && board[1][1] == board[2][2] && board[0][0] != '-') {
    return board[0][0];
  }

  if (board[0][2] == board[1][1] && board[1][1] == board[2][0] && board[0][2] != '-') {
    return board[0][2];
  }

  // No winner yet.
  return -1;
}
```

You can use these functions as a starting point to write your own Tic Tac Toe game in C.</response>

